      Rochedale is one of Brisbane's most consistent family suburbs in the southeastern corridor, offering a mix of modern masterplanned estates, the established Rochedale State School and Rochedale State High catchments, and a quieter acreage character in the older eastern pockets. It attracts upgraders from across the inner south and southeastern suburbs along with interstate family buyers comparing south Brisbane against the Gold Coast corridor.
    </p>
